An Act to improve access, opportunity, and capacity in Massachusetts vocational-technical
education.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1.
2 EXECUTIVE OFFICE OF EDUCATION
3 Office of the Secretary
4 XXXX-XXXX For a competitive grant program to be administered by the executive
5 office of education, in consultation with the executive office of economic development and the
6 executive office of labor and workforce development, to provide capital and equipment funding
7 to expand high quality Chapter 74 career technical education and training programs in high-
8 demand, high-wage fields that are aligned to the commonwealth’s Regional Labor Market
9 Blueprints; provided that grant funds may be used for capital and equipment expenditures
10 including, but not limited to, construction of additions or new buildings, start-up lease costs,
