11 improvement of existing infrastructure, demolition and removal of existing structures, and
12 purchase of equipment; provided further that grant funds may not be used to pay staff salaries,
13 professional development costs, or travel expenses, purchase school vehicles, or to offset
14 overhead costs; provided further, that vocational technical schools, agricultural high schools, and
15 comprehensive high schools offering no less than five Chapter 74 programs shall be eligible for
16 funds from this program; provided further, that eligible recipients shall be located in regions of
17 the commonwealth with wait lists for enrollment in Chapter 74 programs; provided further, that
18 funds may support the duplication by a comprehensive high school of existing Chapter 74
19 programs within a regional vocational-technical school district so long as there is demonstrated
20 student and labor market demand for said program and the regional vocational-technical school
21 district is unable to meet said demand; provided further, that preference in awarding grants shall
22 be given to: (i) schools serving Gateway Cities, (ii) schools with existing Chapter 74 programs in
23 high-demand, high-wage fields that have an excess of applications over seats, (iii) schools with
24 demonstrated strong connections to regional employers, and (iv) schools which have received
25 Chapter 74 program approval by the Department of Elementary and Secondary Education and
26 have a demonstrated ability to promptly expand capacity to implement said program; provided
27 further, that no individual grant award shall exceed $25,000,000; provided further that initial
28 term of said grant program shall be three years; provided further that not less than $100,000,000
29 shall be awarded per year during the initial term; provided further, that the executive office of
30 education, in consultation with the executive office of economic development and the executive
31 office of labor and workforce development, shall adopt additional guidelines as necessary for the
32 administration of the program; and provided further that funds for this Section shall come from
