36 SECTION 2. Section 10 of Chapter 70B of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022
37 Official Edition, is hereby amended by adding the following new subsection:
38 (d) Notwithstanding any state law, state regulation, or agency policy to the contrary, the
39 authority shall be authorized and directed to add twenty (20) percentage points to the project
40 reimbursement rates for regional vocational-technical high school and county, regional and
41 independent agricultural high school construction so that reimbursement rates for such projects
42 are not less than 75% nor more than 90% of the eligible costs. Further, the authority shall add
43 five (5) percentage points to the reimbursement rate for any project that includes state-approved
44 vocational-technical education programs as defined in Chapter 74 of the General Laws aligned
45 with priorities specifically identified in the Regional Labor Market Blueprint for the region in
46 which the school is located. However, additional percentage points shall not be awarded unless
47 the school currently offers five (5) or more Chapter 74 programs. In no case shall the total
48 reimbursement for a project exceed 90% of eligible costs.
