53 “District of residence”, shall mean the school district of the city or town where a student
54 resides.
55 “School of residence”, shall mean the middle school or junior high school a student
56 attends within their district of residence.
57 Section 39. (a) The department of elementary and secondary education shall develop and
58 implement policies and promulgate regulations to promote, enhance, and expand vocational-
59 technical education programs, as defined in Chapter 74 of the General Laws, in the
60 commonwealth.
61 (b) The department shall:
62 (i) oversee all Chapter 74 approved programs and ensure compliance with M.G.L.
63 Chapter 74 and related regulations;
64 (ii) work to increase awareness of vocational-technical education and career opportunities
65 among students in elementary schools, junior high schools, and middle schools;
66 (iii) ensure that schools offering Chapter 74 programs are provided reasonable access
67 during the school day at schools of residence to meet with all students and distribute information
68 about vocational-technical education and careers to said students, including English language
69 learners, students with disabilities, students of color, and other student populations, to ensure that
70 such information is provided equitably to all learners;
71 (iv) ensure that schools offering Chapter 74 programs are given the opportunity during
72 the school day to host middle school tours, with transportation costs paid by the school hosting
73 the tour, for all middle school students in member communities, including English language
